{
  "local_port": 43388,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you clear your Hotmail inbox?",
  "response": "Clearing your Hotmail inbox (now managed through [Outlook.com](https://outlook.live.com/)) can help you organize your emails and free up storage space. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you efficiently clear your inbox:\n\n### **1. Sign In to Your Outlook Account**\n\n1. **Navigate to Outlook.com:**\n   - Go to [Outlook.com](https://outlook.live.com/) using your preferred web browser.\n   \n2. **Enter Your Credentials:**\n   - Input your Hotmail email address and password, then click **Sign in**.\n\n### **2. Access Your Inbox**\n\n- Once signed in, you'll be directed to your **Inbox** where all your emails are listed.\n\n### **3. Select Emails to Delete**\n\nYou have several options to select emails for deletion:\n\n#### **A. Delete All Emails in the Inbox**\n\n1. **Select All Emails:**\n   - At the top left of your email list, click the checkbox. This selects all visible emails on the current page.\n   \n2. **Expand Selection (if applicable):**\n   - If you have multiple pages of emails, a prompt like \"Select all conversations in Inbox\" may appear. Click it to select every email in your inbox.\n   \n3. **Delete the Selected Emails:**\n   - Click the **Delete** (trash can) icon located in the toolbar above your emails.\n\n#### **B. Delete Specific Emails**\n\n1. **Manually Select Emails:**\n   - Click the checkbox next to each email you wish to delete.\n   \n2. **Delete the Selected Emails:**\n   - After selecting, click the **Delete** icon in the toolbar.\n\n#### **C. Use Sweep or Filters for Bulk Actions**\n\n1. **Sweep Feature:**\n   - Hover over an email from a specific sender, click on the three-dot **More actions** icon, and select **Sweep**.\n   - Choose to delete all emails from that sender or manage them according to your preference.\n   \n2. **Create Rules:**\n   - Click on the **Settings** (gear icon) > **View all Outlook settings** > **Mail** > **Rules**.\n   - Create a rule to automatically delete or move emails based on specific criteria.\n\n### **4. Empty the Deleted Items Folder**\n\nDeleted emails are moved to the **Deleted Items** folder and still consume storage space until permanently removed.\n\n1. **Navigate to Deleted Items:**\n   - In the left sidebar, scroll down and click on **Deleted Items**.\n\n2. **Empty the Folder:**\n   - Click **Empty folder** at the top, then confirm the action when prompted.\n\n   *Alternatively, to delete specific items:*\n   - Select the emails you want to permanently remove and click **Delete** again or **Erase**.\n\n### **5. Confirm Permanent Deletion (Optional)**\n\nIf you want to ensure that deleted emails can't be recovered:\n\n1. **Go to the Deleted Items Folder:**\n   - As above, navigate to **Deleted Items**.\n\n2. **Permanently Delete Specific Emails:**\n   - Select the emails, right-click, and choose **Delete forever**.\n\n3. **Empty the Folder Completely:**\n   - Click **Empty folder** to remove all items permanently.\n\n### **6. Additional Tips**\n\n- **Archive Instead of Delete:**\n  - If you're unsure about permanently deleting emails, consider archiving them. Select the emails and click the **Archive** icon. Archived emails are moved out of the inbox but remain accessible.\n\n- **Organize with Folders:**\n  - Create folders to categorize important emails, reducing inbox clutter without deleting messages.\n\n- **Regular Maintenance:**\n  - Periodically review and clean your inbox to prevent accumulation of unwanted emails.\n\n### **Using the Outlook Desktop App or Mobile App**\n\nIf you prefer using the Outlook desktop application or the mobile app, the steps are similar:\n\n1. **Open the App and Sign In:**\n   - Launch the Outlook app and log into your Hotmail/Outlook account.\n\n2. **Navigate to Inbox:**\n   - Access your inbox where your emails are listed.\n\n3. **Select Emails:**\n   - Use the selection tools (checkboxes or long-press) to select multiple emails.\n\n4. **Delete and Empty Deleted Items:**\n   - Delete selected emails and ensure you empty the **Deleted Items** folder to free up space.\n\n### **Caution**\n\n- **Permanent Deletion:**\n  - Once you empty the **Deleted Items** folder, recovering those emails is typically not possible. Ensure you truly want to remove them before doing so.\n\n- **Important Emails:**\n  - Double-check that you're not deleting important or necessary emails. Consider using the **Archive** feature for emails you might need later but don't want cluttering your inbox.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively clear and manage your Hotmail/Outlook inbox, keeping your email organized and streamlined.",
